This paper discusses a new dual stack scheme for protecting return addresses in memory unsafe languages, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a full integration into the LLVM compiler framework, which is a software engineering topic (cs.SE). The implementation involves modifications to the stack, which is a programming languages topic (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the feasibility and practicality of the approach, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
